newsitem.title: TAIWAN: Taiwan money rates close lower; downtrend seen.
newsitem.headline: Taiwan money rates close lower; downtrend seen.

text.p: Taiwan's money rates closed lower on Tuesday as market liquidity remained loose on routine monthly payrolls returning to the banking system, dealers said.

The overnight interbank rate ended at 4.979 percent against Monday's 4.988 close, with 30-day commercial paper at 5.00 against 5.05-5.10. Dealers said they expected both rates to linger near the 5.00 level in the near future.
The bond market saw no transaction in the afternoon.
The 10-year 84/1 bond yield ended morning trade at 5.650 against 5.645-5.650, and the seven-year 85/3 bond yield was at 5.555-5.560. -- Julie Hu (5080815)
